    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "`let` is not hoisted to the top of the function. Meaning you can now safely have `let` variables scoped inside `if` and `while` without any collision risk with a variable defined in a higher scope.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-11-12T10:53:57Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/429#issuecomment-156072022",
